ml

Class SiblingReorderMaxentModel

  • java.lang.Object
    • ml.StanfordMaxentModelImplementation
      • ml.SiblingReorderMaxentModel

  • public class SiblingReorderMaxentModel
extends StanfordMaxentModelImplementation
    This class implements a maximum entropy model for scoring <l and <r as required to score REORDER transitions (see Eq. 19, Section 4.2.1 Modeling). The maximum entropy model for <* is implemented by ParentChildReorderMaxentModel. See StanfordMaxentModelImplementation for further details on the implemented methods. The features used by toDatumList(Amr, Vertex, boolean) are explained in the thesis.
